				\begin{document}$k_{2}$\end{document} values observed for Mars at the Solar tidal periods may only be explained by a core in a primarily, if not entirely, liquid state (Yoder et al. 2003). The most recent determinations of the tidal Love number from orbiters have furthermore narrowed our estimation of the Mars core. The last proposed value for k2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
