				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$M=10^{15}~\mbox{N}\,\mbox{m}$\end{document} moment (Fig. 2). For S waves, the amplitude peak will occur at longer period and for one octave around 0.1 Hz, with a ratio of about 5. This illustrates the fulfillment of requirement L2-7b of Table 3.

Last but not least and as noted in Sect. A.5 of Appendix A, an event large enough to create observable excitation of the planet’s free oscillation (seismic moment of ∼1018Nm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
