				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$T>15\mbox{--}20~\mbox{s}$\end{document}) and possibly at short period during the day. The efficiency of pressure decorrelation proposed by Murdoch et al. (2017b) will likely improve significantly the detection and analysis of quakes. This is illustrated with synthetic waveforms realized for the Marsquake Service blind test (Clinton et al. 2017), which include realistic pressure noise from Large Eddy Simulation. Figure 8 shows the benefit on the largest quake in the blind test catalog: Mw=5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
