The TCDM will have to be tuned regularly, e.g. every few months, in order to accommodate the seasonal changes on Mars, as the sensor’s sensitivity is expected to vary with temperature. This is illustrated by the neutral line in Fig. 46, where the apparent temperature VBB sensitivity varies from −2×10−5m/s2/K\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
