Table 12 shows that the sensor thermal sensitivity requirement is met, both for the uncorrected SP output and after regression of the SP output against temperature, where the residue is set by the uncertainty in the sensitivity. The thermoelastic sensitivity is not an SP requirement, but the effect at 0.1 Hz can be estimated using the SEIS model value of the external temperature noise under the WTS of 3×10−6K/Hz\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
