The MEMS Tilt sensor is based on an ADXL203 built by Analog Devices. This is an high precision, low power, complete dual-axis accelerometer with signal conditioned voltage outputs, all on a single, monolithic integrated circuit. The ADXL203 measures acceleration with a full-scale range of ±1.7(Earth)g\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
